	(text "* Usage of this IC is optional, but recommended,\n  as it allows for setting up the board for programming\n  with a single button (i.e., the RESET button).\n* When RESET button is pressed for at least 7.5s,\n  BOOT line will be forced high, and will enable SoC\n  boot from system memory once ~{RST} is deasserted.\n* The capacitor and resistor on BOOT line are just\n  assurances in case anything goes wrong, or if the\n  IC is deemed unnecessary."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 97.79 99.06 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "66220883-14ad-45fa-8608-de2a0c3536a0")
	)
	(text "* Usage of this IC is totally optional.\n  It can be left un-populated if not needed.\n* When ~{BTN} is pressed for at least 7.5s,\n  ~{RST} will be forced low.\n* Keep ~{BTN} pressed for at least 8.5s and\n  the Power Path IC will also reset and\n  force the whole board to power-cycle."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 97.79 55.88 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "75a195b9-9a4a-471a-b42f-ef4b849cb51d")
	)
